N gram language model is a probabilistic language model, used to predict next word.
It's a sequences of n-items in a sentence, where n can be a positive integer
n = 1 >>> monogram 
n = 2 >>> bigram
n = 3 >>> trigram
and so on
This file describes two ways to generate n-grams in Python.
The first way: using Python 
The second way: using NLTK package
